replies.body:
My primary champions:

{{champion:102}} 
{{champion:17}} 
{{champion:22}} 
{{champion:90}} 
{{champion:89}} 
{{champion:16}} 

You can check my mastery points on those.

I have never once felt they were more unfair than Twitch appearing and going "pew pew pew your team is now dead." or Brand just going "QWER your team is dead." when ahead.

In fact, when Fiora or Riven are ahead. I can simply go. "Oh you are in melee range? Let me..." {{summoner:3}} Then they do no damage and die shortly after. I cannot exhaust Caitlyn from 650 units away.

{{champion:103}}{{champion:38}}{{champion:85}}{{champion:8}}{{champion:115}}
These are the ones that have an escape and more or less the safety of range.

{{champion:245}}{{champion:105}}{{champion:38}}
These are melee and either need their mobility to engage, escape or both.

{{champion:13}}{{champion:4}}{{champion:268}}{{champion:60}}{{champion:136}}{{champion:163}}
These are the ones with a conditional escape ability. You can stop Ryze from ulting away, unless he used Zhonyas. You can cc (or simply kill) TF while he's channeling. You can bodyblock Azirs dash. Elise can only Rapple onto enemy units, and Aurelion Sol and Taliyah can't use their spells in a fight.

{{champion:69}}{{champion:134}}{{champion:143}}{{champion:45}}{{champion:136}}{{champion:61}} 
Have strong AoE CC that they can use as a disengage. They still have to run away however, due to the lack of mobility abilities.

{{champion:101}}{{champion:161}}{{champion:136}}{{champion:163}}{{champion:115}}
Are usually dead when some melee carry or fighter is on top of them.

And of course:
Zhonyas is a damn traitor that will stab you in the back. It makes you completely unable to get away from bad situations, and is best used to avoid dying in the clusterfuck that is a teamfight. It will not save you from a juggernaut/assassin/skirmisher running your way, unless they are stupid enough to run through your whole team first. It usually just prolongs the inevitable (which I actually find rather fitting, but whatever).
The only champions that can use Zhonyas and still have some means of self-protection are {{champion:9}}{{champion:50}}{{champion:136}} and other champions that have a non-channeled damage- or escape ability (Ryze) that lasts either until toggled off, or until it's duration finished.
